Program: Outlook
Title: 14/06/2012
Link: https://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/p00t2h23
Last Broadcast Date: Fri 15 Jun 2012
Extraordinary personal stories from around the world. Today, Musa Aliyu, the Nigerian Muslim who took on an armed mob to rescue a Christian woman. He was nearly killed himself as a result, but survived and now works to bring peace to his homeland. Also, the Brazilian man who's followed his dream and established a library in the slums of Rio de Janeiro; and Malian musician Ben Zabo tells us about his songs of peace and tolerance. His debut album, Ben Zabo, is out now. (Image: Otavio Junior lives in a favela in Rio De Janeiro) Show less